## Publish to the MCP Registry

This project ships registry-ready metadata:

1. Edit `server.json`: replace `YOUR-DOMAIN` with your deployed domain{% if github_owner == "YOUR-GITHUB-USERNAME" %} and `YOUR-GITHUB-USERNAME` with your GitHub user/org{% endif %}.
2. Make sure the server is publicly reachable at the `remotes[].url`.
3. Push a version tag: `git tag v1.0.0 && git push --tags`.

`.github/workflows/publish-mcp.yml` authenticates via GitHub OIDC and publishes
to the official registry (registry.modelcontextprotocol.io), which feeds the
marketplaces MCP clients use for discovery.
